<table width="1160" border="0"><tr><td width="302" height="255"><img src="../Pictures/cheetahs.png" width="300" height="253" alt="Cheetahs Photo"></td><td width="848"><p id ="main_contents">The world's fastest land mammal can go 45 miles per hour in  5 seconds. Cheetah's coats are<br><br><br>golden with many small black spots and their tails are long with black bands and a white tip.<br><br><br><strong>Size:</strong> Cheetahs are about 3 1/2 to 41/2 feet in length, not including their tail. Males tend to<br><br><br>be much larger and weight 10 pounds more than females.<br><br><br><strong>Habitat:</strong> Savannas, need open areas so they can stalk and chase.<br><br><br><strong>National Zoo Diet:</strong> The Zoo's cheetahs eat such things as beef, rabbits and chickens.</p></td></tr></table></div></div>
	
